# Responsive Food Ordering Website

This project is a responsive food ordering website with a navigation bar, home section, and an order section showcasing different food items. The website is built using HTML and CSS.

## Features

- Responsive Navigation Bar
- Home Section with a Welcome Card
- Order Section with Food Items
- Mobile-friendly Design

## Technologies Used

- HTML
- CSS

## Fonts

The website uses the following fonts from Google Fonts:
- Bree Serif
- Caveat
- Lobster
- Monoton
- Open Sans
- Playfair Display SC
- Playfair Display
- Roboto
- Source Sans Pro
- Work Sans

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- A web browser to view the website.

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd your-repo-name
Usage
Open the index.html file in your web browser to view the website.
Responsive Design
The website is designed to be responsive. The navigation links and icons are hidden on mobile devices, and a menu toggle button is displayed. The order section displays food items in a column layout on mobile devices and in a row layout on larger devices.

Media Queries
The following media query is used to make the website responsive:

css
Copy code
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-links {
        display: none;
        flex-direction: column;
        width: 100%;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .nav-links.active {
        display: flex;
    }

    .nav-icons {
        display: none;
    }

    .menu-toggle {
        display: flex;
    }

    .item-card-container {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }
}
